  "body": "- [x ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue [here](https://gitter.im/ConsenSys/truffle?at=5b66a67c5d1362758b34ed67) and once more previously, cannot find too much to scroll.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nTesting.\r\nABI.\r\nDerived class.\r\nCannot call the method in the derived class.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n#### Base.sol\r\n\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.23;\r\n\r\ncontract Base {\r\n  function bid() {\r\n\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Derived.sol\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.23;\r\n\r\nimport \"./Base.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract Derived is Base {\r\n  function bid(uint number) {\r\n\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### testing.js\r\n```\r\nconst Derived = artifacts.require('Derived.sol')\r\n\r\ncontract('Testing', function (accounts) {\r\n  let owner = accounts[0]\r\n  let bidderA = accounts[1]\r\n\r\n  let derived;\r\n\r\n  beforeEach(async function() {\r\n    derived = await Derived.new({from: owner});\r\n  });\r\n\r\n  it('Should be able to call bid without a parameter', async function() {\r\n    await derived.bid({from: bidderA });\r\n  })   \r\n\r\n  it('Should be able to call bid with parameter', async function() {\r\n    await derived.bid(123, {from: bidderA });\r\n  })  \r\n\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nStack Overflow question - https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/55709/error-invalid-number-of-arguments-to-solidity-function-im-pretty-sure-the-nu - at first I thought I do something wrong, realised I should report a bug.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nShould be able to call the derived method with an additional argument.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n> Error: Invalid number of arguments to Solidity function\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: MacOs\r\n* Ethereum client:\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`):\r\n`Truffle v4.1.13 (core: 4.1.13)`\r\n`Solidity v0.4.24 (solc-js)`\r\n* node version (`node --version`): `v9.5.0`\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): `5.6.0`\r\n",
