    "body": "Hi @stefek99.\r\n\r\nThis is supported in the Web3 1.0 version of `truffle-contract` which will ship with Truffle V5. You can check out a prerelease of that by running:\r\n```\r\nnpm install truffle@next\r\n```\r\nUsage notes can be found at PR #1129 (see the Web3 1.0 section). NB: there are some breaking changes. ... \r\n\r\nThe syntax for function overloading is:\r\n```javascript\r\nexample.methods['setValue(uint256)'](123);\r\nexample.methods['setValue(uint256,uint256)'](11,55); \r\n```\r\n\r\nDuplicate of #737.",
